    "recap_text": "IOWA CITY, IOWA-\nSt. Thomas baseball\u00a0team traveled to Iowa City to take on the Iowa Hawkeyes in a midweek matchup. The Tommies ended up falling to the Hawkeyes 5-2.\nAdam Puder\nand\nMax Berrisford\nrecorded RBIs for the Tommies, and Puder tallied the two Tommie hits.\nScoring Summary:\nIowa stuck first plating a run in the bottom half of the first.\u00a0The next three innings were\u00a0scoreless\u00a0on both sides before Iowa\u00a0plated two more runs to go up 3-0.\nThe Hawkeyes then plated\u00a0two more\u00a0runs\u00a0in the bottom\u00a0of\u00a0the sixth to take a\u00a05-0 lead.\nThe\u00a0Tommies\u00a0put two\u00a0on the board\u00a0in\u00a0the top of the seventh when\nAdam Puder\ns double scored\nLucas McNellis\n, and a sac fly from\nMax Berrisford\nscored\nChris Knowles\n.\nIowa then\u00a0responded by plating two runs of\u00a0their\u00a0own in the bottom of eighth, taking a 7-2 lead.\nUp Next\nThe\u00a0Tommies\u00a0will open up Summit League play on the road at Northern Colorado March 13-15.\nFollow Along\nAny and all information\u00a0pertaining to\u00a0the St. Thomas baseball team can be found at tommiesports.com and on Twitter @TommieBase and Instagram at @TommieBaseball."
